                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/mime-526" class="program-course-title">
              MIME 526 Mineral Economics (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-30416" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Mining &amp; Materials Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Mining &amp; Materials Engineering              : Mineral project evaluation techniques and applications. Topics covered include grade-tonnage relationships, capital and operating cost estimation techniques, assessment of mineral market conditions, taxation, discounted cash flow analysis, risk analysis, and optimization of project specifications with respect to capacity and cutoff grade.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
